dismissalText.commentary: Jacques Kallis lbw b Larsen 53 (66b 6x4 1x6 85m) SR: 80.3

notes: New Zealand innings: 50 off 74 balls, 53 minutes; 100 off 152 balls, 109 minutes; 150 off 228 balls, 162 minutes; 200 off 287 balls, 206 minutes.
RG Twose: 50 off 72 balls, 100 minutes, 7x4, 6th ODI 50. It is his 2nd consecutive ODI 50, both scored at Jade Stadium, Christchurch.

RG Twose and AC Parore 4th wicket partnership: 50 off 81 balls, 60 minutes; 100 off 145 balls, 99 minutes. 102 is the best 4th wicket partnership in ODIs for New Zealand against South Africa (previous best: 46 between BA Young and CL Cairns at Hobart in 1993-94).
South Africa innings: 50 off 64 balls, 47 minutes; 100 off 117 balls, 86 minutes; 150 off 199 balls, 143 minutes; 200 off 232 balls, 167 minutes.
JH Kallis: 50 off 60 balls, 80 minutes, 6x4, 1x6, 10th ODI 50. It is his 3rd consecutive ODI 50+ score.
G Kirsten: 50 off 60 balls, 99 minutes, 7x4, 21st ODI 50.
WJ Cronje: 50 off 45 balls, 53 minutes, 5x4, 2x6, 34th ODI 50.

G Kirsten and JH Kallis 3rd wicket partnership: 50 off 57 balls, 41 minutes; 100 off 114 balls, 81 minutes. 103 is the best 3rd wicket partnership in ODIs for South Africa against New Zealand (previous best: 80 between DJ Callaghan and DJ Cullinan at Centurion in 1994-95).

G Kirsten and WJ Cronje 4th wicket partnership: 50 off 69 balls, 49 minutes; 100 off 104 balls, 72 minutes. 109* is the best 4th wicket partnership in ODIs for South Africa against New Zealand (previous best: 85 between PN Kirsten and DJ Cullinan at Brisbane in 1993-94).
